oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Juvenile bovine angiomatosis: A syndrome of young cattle
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Watson, T. D. G.
Thompson, H.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: angiomatous lesions
clinical features
pathological features
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This report describes the clinical and pathological features associated with angiomatous lesions in two calves. In the first case, a single mass located in the atrioventricular ring of the heart was responsible for congestive cardiac failure.
